{"by":"dwedge","id":47771829,"parent":47768195,"text":"I&#x27;m torn on this. It should go through the courts, but the fact is that cloudflare are providing access to illegal content and not doing anything about it.<p>Spain were left with two choices if Cloudflare refuse to act. Either accept it (oh well, too big to fail), or block them.<p>I dislike what is happening but I kind of like that Spain don&#x27;t care about the size of Cloudflare and hold them as accountable as they would a small hosting company in Belarus. Blocking entire ranges due to illegal content isn&#x27;t exactly new, the scale is new.<p>Again though, I really dislike that it isn&#x27;t going through the legal system","time":1776202639,"type":"comment"}